<subSubSection lastPageId="99" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="98.[151,1437,1878,2013]" lastBlockId="99.[151,1437,150,465]" lastPageId="99" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,617,1986,2012]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Distribution: WEST PALAEARCTIC:</emphasis>
Circum-Mediterranean, 
<collectingCountry box="[897,974,1987,2013]" name="Russia" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[987,1068,1987,2013]" name="Turkey" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, Caucasus (
<bibRefCitation author="Rasmont, P." box="[1202,1372,1986,2013]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" pagination="3 - 20" refId="ref106061" refString="Rasmont, P. (1995) Les Anthophores de France du sous-genre Lophanthophora Brooks avec la redescription de trois especes au statut confus (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Anthophoridae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, New Series,, 31 (1), 3 - 20." type="journal article" year="1995">Rasmont 1995</bibRefCitation>
). The possible presence of the species in Central Asia is unclear.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,150,465]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Brooks, R. W." box="[222,387,186,212]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" pagination="436 - 575" refId="ref100587" refString="Brooks, R. W. (1988) Systematics and phylogeny of the Anthophorine bees (Hymenoptera Anthophoridae; Anthophorini). The university of Kansas Bulletin, 53 (9), 436 - 575." type="journal article" year="1988">Brooks (1988)</bibRefCitation>
initiated a very confusing situation in mixing this taxon with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gribodo. These" authorityName="Gribodo. These" authorityYear="1873" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Anthophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mucida">
<emphasis box="[1102,1326,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Anthophora mucida</emphasis>
Gribodo. These
</taxonomicName>
species are nevertheless well distinct. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rasmont, P." box="[646,826,222,249]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" pagination="3 - 20" refId="ref106061" refString="Rasmont, P. (1995) Les Anthophores de France du sous-genre Lophanthophora Brooks avec la redescription de trois especes au statut confus (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Anthophoridae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, New Series,, 31 (1), 3 - 20." type="journal article" year="1995">Rasmont (1995)</bibRefCitation>
made a complete re-description of both taxa and of the similar 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski." authorityName="Radoszkowski." box="[236,631,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Anthophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agama">
<emphasis box="[236,453,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Anthophora agama</emphasis>
Radoszkowski.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rasmont, P." box="[645,825,258,285]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" refId="ref106300" refString="Rasmont, P. (2014 b) Atlas of the European Bees: genus Anthophora. 1 st Edition. STEP Project, Atlas Hymenoptera, Mons, Gembloux. http: // www. atlashymenoptera. net / page. aspx? ID = 260 (accessed 10 November 2020)" type="url" year="2014">Rasmont 2014b</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
